result.execSummary:
The defendant Alicia Moreno-Hernandez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: To pay the costs of the action.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. To pay supervision fees as ordered by the Dept. of Corrections.
Maintain full-time employment as directed by probation agent.
Maintain absolute sobriety from alcohol. No contact with victims (husband or children) without consent of husband, probation agent and Door County Dept. of Human Services.

Complete any counseling, evaluations, programs and assessments, including AODA assessment, as appropriate resulting from the Department's COMPAS assessment. Submit a DNA sample to the State of Wisconsin with 10 days.

records.addlTxt: Minute sheet. Defense waives reading of the Information.  State gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters guilty plea to Ct. 2.  Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds pleas made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts pleas, and finds guilty of Ct. 2.  Court dismisses remaining counts but reads in for sentencing. Court reviews collateral consequences, possible penalties for felony conviction with defendant. Defendant must submit a DNA sample to the State of Wisconsin w/in 10 days and pay the $250 DNA surcharge. State/Defense ready to proceed to sentencing without the benefit of a PSI. State/Defense make sentencing statement. Bond is no longer in effect.

Defendant Alicia Moreno-Hernandez in court with attorney Luca Lopes Fagundes.  Defendant Alicia Moreno-Hernandez in custody.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Reme Bashi interprets for defendant, sworn. Defense waives right to Prelim. Court questions defendant on waiver. Court finds waiver made freely and voluntarily, accepts waiver and binds over for trial. Court finds probable cause for bindover.
Defendant was fingerprinted on 3/7/14. (fingerprint card destroyed 4/03/14)

Defendant Alicia Moreno-Hernandez in court, in custody.  Raymond L. Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Reme Bashi appeared as Interpreter, sworn.  Court reviews charges, max. penalties, right to counsel, right to prelim. Bond continues as is.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for April 1, 2014 at 08:30 am.
No contact direct or indirect with her children, her husband AD, the residence at 1417 Iowa Drive.  Maintain absolute sobriety from alcohol.
